      "author_steamid": "76561198778630932",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 0,
      "playtime_at_review": 90,
      "review_text": "The game is about a girl named Ann who has been searching for her sister, who has been missing for 7 months. It’s a really cool game that combines RPG and Bullet Hell gameplay. \nYou explore the town for clues about your sister’s whereabouts, and if you run into an enemy, the game switches to a bullet hell mini-game. These mini-games aren't too hard, but if you going for a no damage run it might be brutal to do. The game also has beautiful pixel art graphics and a really catchy soundtrack that I plan to buy.\nI definitely Recommend giving the game a go",
      "timestamp_created": 1774059255
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221239826",
      "author_steamid": "76561198081847407",
      "voted_up": true,
      "votes_up": 0,
      "playtime_at_review": 55,
      "review_text": "I was going to play the demo since I'm still catching up on Steam Next Fest demos, but it was taken down, cuz the game finally released. I couldn't play too much due to a headache, but enjoyed what I played so far! Cute art and the combat felt very Undertale-y. I'll update my review once I've played more! \n\nStream when I played it (Live thoughts):\nhttps://www.twitch.tv/videos/2727564849\nhttps://youtube.com/live/g6suVCT5V9A",
      "timestamp_created": 1774075096
    }
